BAUCHI – A group known as the APC Youth Progressive Forum has canvassed support for Senator Umaru Tanko Al-Makura representing the Nasarawa Central Senatorial District, to lead the All Progressives Congress (APC) as National Chairman. The National Chairman of the Group, Hon Ukkasha Hamza Rahama, who stated this on Thursday, during a press conference in Bauchi, said that it is unarguable that among all the contenders for the office of the APC National Chairman, Senator Al-Makura remains the only dependable, reliable, trustworthy and the best option, to salvage the party and return it to winning ways in the 2023 anticipated General elections. Describing Al-Makura as one of the founding fathers of the APC and his contributions to the success of President Muhammadu Buhari administration, Honourable Ukkasha said that the Senator had been tested and trusted both at the grassroots and state levels to deliver the mandate of APC as he performed excellently when he served as a Governor of Nasarawa state and currently a senator of the Federal Republic of Nigeria. Environmental Laws Enforced At Yuletide In Ondo To Forestall… Asus Unveils ZenBook 14X OLED Space Edition To Nigerian Market “As it stands, new have many of our party members who have indicated interest to view for the exalted office as the National Chairman. We are mindful of the fact that some of our stakeholders from the North-East region reached out to us on the need to support the emergence of the APC National Chairman from the region. “As those who made outstanding sacrifices to see that the All Progressive Congress see the light of the day, using our energy and resources, we are left with no other option than to support only a candidate who can do the job, most especially at this crucial moment. The person with this requisite experience is the former Governor of Nasarawa state and a member of the current 9th Senate Distinguished Senator Umaru Tanko Al-Makura. “We shall continue to support the realization of this goal so that the unborn generations will read and borrow from the APC National archives that we have made outstanding sacrifices for credibility to emerge by supporting Senator Al-Makura candidature during the party’s historic National Convey come February 2022” “We are looking beyond our region in the North-East and travel far away to Nasarawa state to identify ourselves with Al-Makura, believing that he has all the requisite experience to advance the course of the ruling APC and sustaining it gains and securing the future” “We have made extensive consultations within the party hierarchy, women groups, youth associations and stakeholders within the ruling APC, particularly the National Delegates in the North-East, other parts of the geo-political zones and the level of commitment towards this glaring move, gave is more hope and confidence that Senator Al-Makura will return elected in the party’s National convention come February In-Sha Allah,” he said.